30006927@@@@@@1 Background@@@@1@2@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1748@LMC@2019-06-15
30006928@@@@@@Nanyang Technological University (NTU) has organised a free shuttle bus service for the convenience of students who reside in relatively distant regions [1].@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1749@LMC@2019-06-15
30006929@@@@@@The service utilise direct route buses to help these students reduce travelling time to school.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1750@LMC@2019-06-15
30006930@@@@@@However, this initiative has not been effective.@@@@1@7@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1751@LMC@2019-06-15
30006931@@@@@@2 Problem@@@@1@2@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1752@LMC@2019-06-15
30006932@@@@@@The effectiveness of the current shuttle bus service is inhibited by two key issues.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1753@LMC@2019-06-15
30006933@@@@@@Firstly, there are insufficient number of seats to cater to all users.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1754@LMC@2019-06-15
30006934@@@@@@Consequently, students who wish to use the service are compelled to start queuing much earlier in order to board the bus.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1755@LMC@2019-06-15
30006935@@@@@@Secondly, students can only verify seat availability in person.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1756@LMC@2019-06-15
30006936@@@@@@As a result, students unable to board the bus end up making a fruitless trip to the pickup point before taking their own transport.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1757@LMC@2019-06-15
30006937@@@@@@3 Solution@@@@1@2@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1758@LMC@2019-06-15
30006938@@@@@@An online platform will be created on NTU’s existing student portal (‘iNTU’) to address both key issues.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1759@LMC@2019-06-15
30006939@@@@@@The platform allow students to indicate their weekly preferences for taking shuttle buses to the NTU management, which can be done by directly accessing iNTU or using mobile applications such as ‘NTU Mobile’ (see Figure 1).@@@@1@36@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1760@LMC@2019-06-15
30006940@@@@@@After collating the students’ indicated preferences, the NTU management can use these data to estimate the number of buses required to meet daily demand.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1761@LMC@2019-06-15
30006941@@@@@@In addition, the platform allow students to opt to receive updates on seat availability via WhatsApp (see Figure 2).@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1762@LMC@2019-06-15
30006942@@@@@@Figure 1: Existing mobile application: ‘NTU Mobile’ with an added shuttle bus section@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1763@LMC@2019-06-15
30006943@@@@@@Figure 2: WhatsApp group message updating seat availability@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1764@LMC@2019-06-15
30006944@@@@@@4 Benefits@@@@1@2@ntucle-docid:247; ntucle-sid:1765@LMC@2019-06-15
