30007127@@@@@@Title@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1885@LMC@2019-06-15
30007128@@@@@@Tackling Ageism with Technology@@@@1@4@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1886@LMC@2019-06-15
30007129@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1887@LMC@2019-06-15
30007130@@@@@@In view of the ageing population in Singapore (Singapore Department of Statistics (DOS), 2015), coupled with the rapid advancements in technology, it is a growing concern that senior citizens would be unable to catch up with societal changes.@@@@1@38@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1888@LMC@2019-06-15
30007131@@@@@@An exclusive society, ostracism against the older population (Heng, 2013) and an overly-burdened workforce (Ng, 2015) are few of the dreaded consequences.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1889@LMC@2019-06-15
30007132@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1890@LMC@2019-06-15
30007133@@@@@@While there are ongoing initiatives such as workshops to engage the elderly in the usage of computers (Infocomm Development Authority of Singapore, 2015), the steep learning curve coupled with the frequently updated systems deter a considerable number of the older population, particularly first-time users, from picking up relevant technological skills (Telikin, 2015).@@@@1@52@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1891@LMC@2019-06-15
30007134@@@@@@As such, the skills possessed by the pioneer generation may become obsolete, worsening ageism in Singapore.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1892@LMC@2019-06-15
30007135@@@@@@Solution@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1893@LMC@2019-06-15
30007136@@@@@@The main goal of this proposal is to provide a bridging platform to integrate the older population into the digital natives.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1894@LMC@2019-06-15
30007137@@@@@@Silver Operating System (SOS) is a simplified operating system (OS) with features that will ease the process of picking up technological skills for seniors.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1895@LMC@2019-06-15
30007138@@@@@@Firstly, the font sizes and icons will be twice as big as mainstream OS’s by default.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1896@LMC@2019-06-15
30007139@@@@@@In addition, the system supports only basic and more commonly used applications such as Microsoft Office, Microsoft Outlook, Internet Explorer and Adobe Reader (Information Technology Department, 2015).@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1897@LMC@2019-06-15
30007140@@@@@@On mouse over, details and/or instructions of the icon or action will appear to guide the elderly (with multilingual voice command option).@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1898@LMC@2019-06-15
30007141@@@@@@SOS can be downloaded online as a software and upon setup, video tutorials can be played to teach users on how to use the mouse and keyboard.@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1899@LMC@2019-06-15
30007142@@@@@@Benefits@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1900@LMC@2019-06-15
30007143@@@@@@SOS makes computers more elderly-friendly.@@@@1@5@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1901@LMC@2019-06-15
30007144@@@@@@Firstly, as ageing deteriorates one’s eyesight, the enlarged interface minimise strain on the eyes.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1902@LMC@2019-06-15
30007145@@@@@@Next, details and/or instructions given upon mouse over would also provide users with a clearer idea and ease the navigation process.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1903@LMC@2019-06-15
30007146@@@@@@Voice commands could assist the less literate seniors to complete actions.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1904@LMC@2019-06-15
30007147@@@@@@In addition, the limited choices of applications as compared to mainstream OS will make users focus on the more important applications, which helps to minimise confusion concurrently.@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1905@LMC@2019-06-15
30007148@@@@@@After mastering the usage of this simplified OS, the elderly would gain both confidence and the required basic knowledge in using mainstream OS.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1906@LMC@2019-06-15
30007149@@@@@@Implementation@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:251; ntucle-sid:1907@LMC@2019-06-15
