30007170@@@@@@DIY BIOACTIVE PENS for Diabetics@@@@1@5@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1891@LMC@2019-06-15
30007171@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1892@LMC@2019-06-15
30007172@@@@@@Diabetes, caused by either heredity or lifestyle choices, is a silent killer that has threatened people’s lives tremendously.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1893@LMC@2019-06-15
30007173@@@@@@Globally, diabetes has been the 8th leading cause of death for the past decade, affecting both children and adults [1].@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1894@LMC@2019-06-15
30007174@@@@@@It is known to give rise to more disastrous consequences such as heart disease and kidney failure, hence necessitating early diagnosis through constant monitoring of glucose levels before taking steps to reduce cholesterol intake and to exercise regularly.@@@@1@38@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1895@LMC@2019-06-15
30007175@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1896@LMC@2019-06-15
30007176@@@@@@The crucial need for monitoring glucose levels has been realized through the use of glucometers1, which however, have not fulfilled the requirements of easy self-testing and portability.@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1897@LMC@2019-06-15
30007177@@@@@@Glucometers and other existing sensors include non re-usable test strips and lancets; the costs incurred by diabetics on such expensive meters and necessities have deterred users from using the meters regularly [2].@@@@1@32@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1898@LMC@2019-06-15
30007178@@@@@@Additionally, younger users, like children, are intimidated by lancets and blood withdrawal used in glucometers.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1899@LMC@2019-06-15
30007179@@@@@@Therefore, improvements from various angles are indispensable.@@@@1@7@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1900@LMC@2019-06-15
30007180@@@@@@Solution@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1901@LMC@2019-06-15
30007181@@@@@@The aim of this proposal is to introduce DIY bioactive pens containing enzyme-based ink for detecting epidermal glucose levels just by drawing the ink on the skin.@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1902@LMC@2019-06-15
30007182@@@@@@These inks also contain electrically conductive graphite powder, which enable it to act as electrodes and transmit glucose readings wirelessly to a Bluetooth-enabled device such as a mobile phone.@@@@1@29@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1903@LMC@2019-06-15
30007183@@@@@@A specifically tailored smartphone application will allow pre-diabetics and diabetics to continuously keep track of their glucose levels to ensure early treatment.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1904@LMC@2019-06-15
30007184@@@@@@Furthermore, connecting the mobile application with one’s doctor’s email will facilitate the flow of updated patient information and instant medical judgement.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1905@LMC@2019-06-15
30007185@@@@@@Figure 1: Bio catalytic ink being drawn on skin with DIY Bioactive pens while using a smartphone application to monitor glucose levels@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1906@LMC@2019-06-15
30007186@@@@@@(Source: University of California, San Diego, and http://spectrum.ieee.org/tech-talk/biomedical/devices/draw-biosensors-on-your-skin, and Google Images)@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1907@LMC@2019-06-15
30007187@@@@@@Benefits@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1908@LMC@2019-06-15
30007188@@@@@@With the society becoming increasingly tech-savvy, having a smartphone interface raises the understanding patients have of their own medical conditions with simple, informative charts and overviews in the mobile application.@@@@1@30@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1909@LMC@2019-06-15
30007189@@@@@@Ease of use is signified when a pen and a mobile phone are all that is needed for each testing.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1910@LMC@2019-06-15
30007190@@@@@@Secondly, affordability of these pens provides inclusiveness of the whole populace regardless of income.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1911@LMC@2019-06-15
30007191@@@@@@Moreover, the pens allow users to scribble sensors onto skin using one’s own doodle designs, giving rise to ‘diagnostic body art’ [3].@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1912@LMC@2019-06-15
30007192@@@@@@This brings enjoyment and less strain to each testing, especially for children.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1913@LMC@2019-06-15
30007193@@@@@@Implementation@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1914@LMC@2019-06-15
30007194@@@@@@The following course of action will ensure smooth implementation of DIY bioactive pens:@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1915@LMC@2019-06-15
30007195@@@@@@1) Collaboration with University of California San Diego researchers will take place to improve on their raw models of pens containing bio-catalytic inks@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1916@LMC@2019-06-15
30007196@@@@@@2) A joint effort between university researchers and established mobile companies like Apple and Samsung will be taken to ensure smooth transmission of wireless glucose measurements@@@@1@26@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1917@LMC@2019-06-15
30007197@@@@@@3) Software engineers from Savvy Apps Company will design a specific smartphone application, which will be made available to both iOS and Android mobile systems@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1918@LMC@2019-06-15
30007198@@@@@@Costs@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1919@LMC@2019-06-15
30007199@@@@@@Pens containing inks with enzymes, graphite and other adhesives $10 per pen@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1920@LMC@2019-06-15
30007200@@@@@@Smartphone application development (one-time cost) $1,000@@@@1@6@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1921@LMC@2019-06-15
30007201@@@@@@Conclusion@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1922@LMC@2019-06-15
30007202@@@@@@A life-long disease like diabetes is passed down generations, necessitating mass usage of monitoring devices for early prevention.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1923@LMC@2019-06-15
30007203@@@@@@DIY bioactive pens provide fast and easy self-monitoring with an accustomed smartphone interface, without users worrying for affordability, convenience and reliability.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:252; ntucle-sid:1924@LMC@2019-06-15
30007204@@@@@@SmartEyes@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1888@LMC@2019-06-15
30007205@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1889@LMC@2019-06-15
30007206@@@@@@Living in the age of technology, we are empowered with many electronic devices that aid us in our daily activities.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1890@LMC@2019-06-15
30007207@@@@@@These gadgets, notably smartphones, are integral in human livelihood and are continually being upgraded to suit our needs.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1891@LMC@2019-06-15
30007208@@@@@@Smartphones have become the catalyst in shaping key areas of communication, research and entertainment.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1892@LMC@2019-06-15
30007209@@@@@@Recently, research has shown that ‘an average user picks up the device more than 1,500 times a week and spends approximately 3 hours and 16 minutes a day on it’ [1].@@@@1@31@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1893@LMC@2019-06-15
30007210@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1894@LMC@2019-06-15
30007211@@@@@@Given the high consumption rate of smartphones, accompanying problems are also likely to be magnified.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1895@LMC@2019-06-15
30007212@@@@@@As users are increasingly focused on their display screens, little attention is then left to observe their surroundings.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1896@LMC@2019-06-15
30007213@@@@@@This makes them vulnerable to hazards such as road traffic and can even pose as inconvenience to others when they obstruct pathways.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1897@LMC@2019-06-15
30007214@@@@@@For example, surveys have shown that most users have had at least one accident while being too engrossed in their phones [2].@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1898@LMC@2019-06-15
30007215@@@@@@Solution@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1899@LMC@2019-06-15
30007216@@@@@@In order to enhance safety and awareness of users, SmartEyes is being developed.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1900@LMC@2019-06-15
30007217@@@@@@SmartEyes is essentially a pre-emptive application that aims to warn the user of approaching hazards.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1901@LMC@2019-06-15
30007218@@@@@@Firstly, the software utilizes the smartphone’s radio transmitter to emit waves to the user’s surroundings, which will then be reflected back upon contact with nearby objects.@@@@1@26@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1902@LMC@2019-06-15
30007219@@@@@@Next, depending on the distance of these objects, the waves are being received back into the phone at different intervals.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1903@LMC@2019-06-15
30007220@@@@@@Subsequently, the data obtained allows the application to compute the path of collision as well as the approximate time of possible accident.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1904@LMC@2019-06-15
30007221@@@@@@Finally, a warning signal from a selection of light, sound or vibration will be generated to alert users of incoming hazards, redirecting their attention back to their surroundings.@@@@1@28@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1905@LMC@2019-06-15
30007222@@@@@@Benefits@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1906@LMC@2019-06-15
30007223@@@@@@This application mainly serves as a safety net to protect users from incoming danger.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1907@LMC@2019-06-15
30007224@@@@@@It aims to provide sufficient buffer time to avoid these hazards, with the main intent on saving lives.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1908@LMC@2019-06-15
30007225@@@@@@It especially targets users who have urgent matters to attend to on their phones and those who are less proficient at multi-tasking.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1909@LMC@2019-06-15
30007226@@@@@@Although the application does not replace the need for responsible phone usage, it seeks an alternative path to minimize possible accidents involving distracted users.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1910@LMC@2019-06-15
30007227@@@@@@Implementation@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1911@LMC@2019-06-15
30007228@@@@@@SmartEyes will be developed in the following steps:@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1912@LMC@2019-06-15
30007229@@@@@@1) Software developers will be engaged to tap into the smartphone functions for data collection and computation.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1913@LMC@2019-06-15
30007230@@@@@@2) Research institutions will also be consulted to determine the optimal reaction time needed, via experiments or human behavioral studies.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1914@LMC@2019-06-15
30007231@@@@@@3) Lastly, programmers will integrate this research into the application.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1915@LMC@2019-06-15
30007232@@@@@@It will initially be made optional on online application stores.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1916@LMC@2019-06-15
30007233@@@@@@Subsequently, it will be incorporated as a basic phone function if proven essential.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1917@LMC@2019-06-15
30007234@@@@@@Costs@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1918@LMC@2019-06-15
30007235@@@@@@The estimated cost will be as such:@@@@1@7@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1919@LMC@2019-06-15
30007236@@@@@@Smartphone research $10,000@@@@1@3@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1920@LMC@2019-06-15
30007237@@@@@@Institutional consultation $12,000@@@@1@3@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1921@LMC@2019-06-15
30007238@@@@@@Software design $3,000@@@@1@3@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1922@LMC@2019-06-15
30007239@@@@@@Total $25,000@@@@1@2@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1923@LMC@2019-06-15
30007240@@@@@@Conclusion@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1924@LMC@2019-06-15
30007241@@@@@@In conclusion, the widespread risks involving distracted smartphone users are excessive and in some cases, fatal.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1925@LMC@2019-06-15
30007242@@@@@@The application’s goal is to minimize possible hazards through timely alerts that will allow users to react appropriately.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:253; ntucle-sid:1926@LMC@2019-06-15
